Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 24/03/2025

We at MAperture ("we," "us," or "our") respect your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our services (the "Service"). By using the Service, you agree to these terms.
1. Information We Collect
A. Data You Provide

    Account details: Name, email, username, password (for registration).

    Content: Files, messages, or other data you upload or create.

    Communications: Support requests, feedback, or survey responses.

B. Data We Automatically Collect

    Usage data: IP address, browser type, device info, pages visited, and timestamps.

    Cookies & tracking: We use cookies (small text files) to:

        Keep you logged in.

        Analyze Service performance (e.g., via Google Analytics).

        Personalize ads (if applicable).

C. Data from Third Parties

    Social logins: If you sign in via Google/GitHub, we receive your public profile info.

    Integrations: Data from linked services (e.g., APIs).

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your data to:

    Provide and improve the Service.

    Respond to your requests or inquiries.

    Prevent fraud, spam, or security risks.

    Comply with legal obligations.

    (Optional) Send updates or marketing emails (you can unsubscribe anytime).

3. Data Sharing & Disclosure

We do not sell your data. We may share it only in these cases:

    With your consent: E.g., for third-party integrations.

    Service providers: Partners who help operate the Service (e.g., hosting, analytics), under strict confidentiality agreements.

    Legal compliance: If required by law (e.g., subpoenas, DMCA requests).

    Business transfers: If we’re acquired, user data may transfer to the new owner.

4. Data Security

    We implement safeguards like encryption (SSL/TLS) and access controls.

    No method is 100% secure, but we strive to protect your data.

5. Your Rights

Depending on your location (e.g., GDPR for EU users, CCPA for California), you may:

    Access, correct, or delete your personal data.

    Opt out of marketing emails or cookies (via browser settings).

    Export your data (e.g., request a copy in machine-readable format).

To exercise these rights, contact us at mapertureco@gmail.com.
6. International Data Transfers

    Your data may be processed in countries with different privacy laws. We ensure protections (e.g., GDPR Standard Contractual Clauses).

7. Children’s Privacy

    Our Service is not intended for children under 13. We don’t knowingly collect their data.

8. Changes to This Policy

    We’ll notify you of significant updates (e.g., via email or Service banner). Continued use means you accept the changes.

